benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/allTags - Retrieve account tags

covered: Valid GET requests and default behavior (TC01): successful retrieval, default excludes deleted tags, audit NONE verified
Query parameter coverage: objectType filtering and combinations with includedDeleted and audit (TC02, TC06, TC16)
Audit parameter levels tested: NONE, MINIMAL, FULL and combinations (TC01, TC04, TC05, TC20, TC21)
Empty and not-found states: no-tags empty array and account-not-found scenarios (TC07, TC08, TC25, TC26)
Error handling for malformed accountId and injection attempts: invalid UUID and SQL injection tests (TC09, TC12)
Authorization and security responses: missing/invalid token -> 401 and security edge-case tests (TC10, TC12)
Downstream resilience and timeouts: service unavailable and timeout behaviors (TC11, TC15) and handling of inconsistent dependent data (TC24)
Integration coverage: tag creation and deletion effects verified via other endpoints (TC18, TC19)
Non-functional and scale checks: large dataset performance and concurrency consistency (TC14, TC23)
Response contract checks: Content-Type header and Tag schema conformance assertions (TC27, TC01)
Regression and backward compatibility checks: regression for deleted tags and default-parameter compatibility (TC16, TC17)
Unsupported parameter handling: extra query parameters ignored (TC13)
gaps: Pagination: no tests validate pagination behavior or assert expected behavior when results are large; the guideline item on pagination is not covered
Caching and conditional GET: no tests for ETag, Cache-Control, If-None-Match, 304 Not Modified semantics or cache headers
Rate limiting and throttling: no tests for 429 responses or behavior under request bursts beyond concurrency consistency
Authorization nuance (403): no tests for valid credentials that lack required permissions or insufficient-scope scenarios
Internal server error handling (500): no explicit tests simulating unexpected server errors and verifying safe error messages
Query parameter validation gaps: invalid/unknown objectType values and malformed includedDeleted parameter formats are not tested
Content negotiation and additional headers: Accept header behaviors, Content-Encoding, and other response headers beyond Content-Type are not validated
HTTP method and header edge cases: no tests for method not allowed (405), missing required headers, or malformed header handling
recommendations: Add pagination tests or an explicit assertion that the API is intentionally unpaginated; if pagination is supported later, add page size, offset, and boundary tests
Add caching tests: assert ETag and Cache-Control headers exist, perform conditional GETs with If-None-Match to verify 304 responses and correct cache semantics
Add rate-limiting tests that simulate bursts and verify 429 responses and Retry-After header handling
Add authorization scope tests to cover 403 forbidden cases where credentials are valid but lack required permissions or roles
Simulate 500 Internal Server Error scenarios (for example by mocking DB failures) and assert safe, non-leaking error messages and appropriate status code

Add negative query-parameter tests: supply invalid objectType values, wrong-case values, and malformed includedDeleted inputs (e.g., "yes", "1", "notabool") to validate input validation and error codes
Expand schema-level assertions to check presence and types of required Tag fields (ids, objectId, objectType, tagDefinitionId, audit fields) for both minimal and full audit modes
Add content negotiation tests (Accept header) and validate other important response headers such as Content-Encoding when applicable
Add HTTP method tests (ensure POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE return 405 or appropriate status) and header validation tests for missing or malformed auth headers
Automate performance tests and include them in CI with repeatable fixtures for large result sets; document acceptable response-time thresholds and resource usage limits
